    "body": "Can you provide more context for the problem you're experiencing? It would be helpful to have all of the files and folders from your hardhat project directory.\r\n\r\nI tried to reproduce this but could not.  I created a new basic project, and modified the sample script to append the following lines to the `main()` method:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n  const contract = await Greeter.attach(greeter.address);\r\n  const accounts = await hre.ethers.getSigners();\r\n  const greeting = await contract.connect(accounts[0]).greet({ gasLimit: 760000 });\r\n  console.log(`greeting returned from method: ${greeting}`);\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd then when I execute the script it works as expected:\r\n```console\r\n$ yarn hardhat run scripts/sample-script.js \r\nyarn run v1.22.11\r\n$ /home/gene/dev/hardhat-empty/node_modules/.bin/hardhat run scripts/sample-script.js\r\nDeploying a Greeter with greeting: Hello, Hardhat!\r\nGreeter deployed to: 0x5FbDB2315678afecb367f032d93F642f64180aa3\r\ngreeting returned from method: Hello, Hardhat!\r\nDone in 1.64s.\r\n```",
